


=Description=

"film makers Ian Cheney and Curt Ellis (of "King Corn" fame) 
are in the editing room, finishing up their latest documentary about their 
adventures as pickup truck farmers (more on that in a minute) and other 
urban farms taking root in the Big Apple. Think: a self-sustaining Staten 
Island barge, a 6,000-square-foot market roof garden and window farms 
created by two Manhattan artists. With 7 million new gardens planted in the 
last year, now is clearly the time to be talking about why our cities need 
more farms, gardens, and green spaces. I caught up with film maker/truck 
farmer Ian Cheney to get the scoop. ..."
(http://planetgreen.discovery.com/travel-outdoors/its-a-truck-its-a-farm-and-now-its-going-to-be-a-movie.html)


